title: Volunteers can help clean up the Coast
text:
BILOXI, Miss. (AP) - The annual Mississippi Coastal Clean Up Day in Harrison, Hancock and Jackson counties is set for Oct. 17 from 8 to 11 a.m.
The Sun Herald reports ( http://bit.ly/1VCKiot ) this will be the 27th year for the event. Last year, almost 2,000 volunteers collected 1,603 bags of trash at 47 sites.
Anyone interested in more information or in volunteering can visit www.mscoastalcleanup.org.
Information from: The Sun Herald, http://www.sunherald.com
